  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7 </p>\n<p>Tip: this is to warm your naans<span class=\"text-highlight\"> later (or you can just pop them in the toaster!)</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Boil a kettle then cut the <strong>paneer</strong> into small bite-sized cubes</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Chop the<strong> potatoes</strong> into quarters, then add them to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 15-20 min or until fork-tender</span></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1839.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1839.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1839.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1839.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1839.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>cubed paneer</strong> and<strong> <span class=\"text-highlight\">ground</span> turmeric</strong> and cook for 3-5 min or until golden all over</p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Season generously with <strong>salt</strong>, then once golden, transfer the <strong>paneer</strong> to a bowl and cover with<strong> boiled water</strong> (this helps to soften the paneer!)</span></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1839.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1839.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1839.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
