      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Once the liquid has reduced, add the <strong>baby leaf spinach</strong>, 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[180ml]</span><strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>milk</strong> and the <strong>garam masala </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 3-4 min further or until the spinach has wilted – this is your <strong>Kolkata aloo paneer curry</strong></span></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>mini coriander naans</strong> to a baking tray</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 3 min or until the bread is hot, then butter once out of the oven<br /> </p>",
